Elswick Leather Works (2nd)

Saturday, November 26, 1881.

Goal: Thomas S. Phalp; backs, John T. Hobson and James Gardner; half‑backs, Alexander Marr and John Armstrong; forwards, right‑wing, John P. Cook and Robert Finlay, centres, William A. Coulson (captain) and William Finlay, left‑wing, George McKenzie and John Dixon
